One of the main symbols of Dubai is the world's tallest skyscraper, Burj Khalifa. The tower is made in the form of a stalagmite, in the heart of the metropolis, next to the famous shopping center The Dubai Mall. The tower embodies the spirit of Dubai and symbolizes the grand ambitions of this amazing city.
You will have the opportunity to ascend to the Burj Khalifa observation deck and enjoy the panorama of Dubai. See Dubai from a bird's eye view with the highest resolution telescopes and enjoy the beauty of the skyline from the open terrace. And see the mesmerizing dance of the famous singing fountains.

Dune Bashing
Experience a real Arabian adventure on a desert safari tour. 
Get on a breathtaking ride in the desert, crossing dunes in a comfortable off-road vehicle, like a real world roller coaster - informally known as 'dune bashing'.
During the safari you will have an opportunity to take stunning pictures of the unmistakable desert beauty as well as try out sand boarding in the steep red dunes.
Desert Camp
After the madness of the dune bashing you will arrive at a desert camp where you will be offered comfortable pillows & cushions to sit on with a stage in the middle of the camp.
At the camp you will be served a full course buffet dinner with live bbq as well as a bar and sheesha station available for extra charge.
The cherry on the cake will be a 3 set live entertainment program consisting of a tanura dance show, belly dance show and a fire show.
Additionally, you will be able to dress in local attire for some exciting photo opportunities and also get 'henna' temporary tatoos that are very common amongst women in the gulf.
The desert safari is a must try tour in the UAE for residents and visitors alike.

A Dhow dinner cruise in Dubai Marina is an excellent opportunity to combine sightseeing and a dining experience.

Dubai Marina is in itself a world renowned land mark, and along our sailing route we will see the skyline of JBR, Blue Water Island, Dubai Harbour aswell as Cayan Tower and Ain Dubai.

Onboard you will have a full course dinner with the opportunity to order alcoholic drinks for an extra charge as well as a live entertainment program.

Experience Summary

The Museum of the Future presents an interesting exposition on the potential development of technology in the next 50 years. Here you will see innovations capable of expanding human physical and intellectual capabilities, helping to solve economic and social problems, and changing the climate change scenario for the better by 2071.
The museum presents the greatest inventions and promising prototypes of technological solutions. Unlike conventional polytechnic museums, the Museum of the Future allows you to interact with the exhibits through interactive displays.
The focus is on three key issues of climate change: access to fresh water, food security, and building/modernizing cities. Solving these problems will improve the lives of all humanity and strengthen the global economy.

Experience Summary

Get ready to witness one of the most iconic landmarks of Dubai from a unique perspective at the Dubai Frame, a stunning architectural marvel that offers breathtaking views of the city's past, present, and future.

Located in the heart of Dubai, the Dubai Frame stands tall at 150 meters and is one of the world's largest picture frames. As you step inside, you'll be transported to a journey through time, starting with the city's humble beginnings as a fishing village to its current status as a thriving metropolis.

Take a panoramic elevator to the top and marvel at the stunning views of Dubai's skyline, with landmarks such as the Burj Khalifa and the Dubai Mall in sight. As you descend, you'll be transported to the future, with projections of what the city might look like in the years to come.

In addition to the stunning views, the Dubai Frame also features interactive exhibits that showcase the city's rich history, culture, and achievements. You'll also get to witness the world's largest picture frame from the inside, with glass panels on either side giving you a unique perspective on the city below.

Perfect for families, couples, and tourists, the Dubai Frame is a must-visit attraction that combines history, culture, and modern technology in a fun and interactive way. So why wait? Book your tickets now and get ready to witness Dubai from a whole new perspective at the Dubai Frame.

Aquaventure is truly a legendary waterpark.
Its the holder of the status of the largest waterpark on Planet Earth.

Its truly a conceptual work of art which is a perfect for any age.

The park is absolutely enormous and has more than 30 different rides of all sizes, kinds and for all ages.

The park is also famous for its innovative ways of incorporating marine animals, greenery and a beach into the mix as well as plenty of resturants and snack stations across the park.

Whether you are a young adult looking for adrenaline and action or a family with children there is something for everyone.

The park is not to be missed by anyone who visits or lives in Dubai.

Experience Summary

Visit Ferrari World Abu Dhabi, the largest indoor theme park in the world, awarded by the World Travel Awards. Here you will feel like a real racer! 

Ferrari World theme park is located in Abu Dhabi on an area of 200 thousand square meters. There are over 20 amazing rides which challenge the conventional perception of entertainment.

Formula Rossa is the fastest roller coaster in the world.

The Flying Aces ride allows you to feel yourself in an airplane doing a dead loop.

Other rides are dedicated to Ferrari racing, including a kart track, children's driving school and racing simulators.

You can also see a huge collection of Ferrari cars, take a virtual tour of the Ferrari factory or take a virtual flight over Italy. And, of course, you can buy Ferrari souvenirs.

Experience Summary

Yas Waterworld Abu Dhabi is the largest water park in the Middle East! The water park is located on the island of Yas - a whole entertainment complex.
The water park has 43 different attractions on an area of 15 hectares, a huge swimming pool, water slides, designed for both children and adults. 
Waiting for you the world's first hydro-magnetic slide, Dawwama Tunnel 20 meters high, slides in the form of six intertwined snakes - Slithers Slides, as well as unique suspended slides Bandit Bombers, which use all kinds of light guns, water bombs and other special effects.

Experience Summary

Warner Bros. World Abu Dhabi is one of the world's largest indoor theme parks. The area of the park is more than 150,000 square meters, includes six zones: Warner Bros Plaza, Bedrock, Dynamite Gulch, Cartoon Junction, Gotham City, Metropolis. The park has more than 25 modern attractions for the whole family, as well as many interactive activities. The park is dedicated to movie characters and cartoons from the famous Warner Brothers Hollywood Studios. You will meet your favorite and brave heroes: Superman and Batman, funny characters from animated series - Tom and Jerry, Bugs Bunny, Scooby-Doo and the Flintstones family, as well as legends from Warner Bros.
There are restaurants, stores, and cafes throughout the park where you'll have a great time!

Experience Summary

Iconic Attraction
Get ready to dive into an underwater world like no other at The Dubai Mall Aquarium, one of the most spectacular and awe-inspiring attractions in Dubai.

With its massive size and diverse collection of marine life, the aquarium offers a unique opportunity to get up close and personal with some of the most fascinating creatures of the ocean.

Walk through a 48-meter-long tunnel and gaze in amazement at
over 140 species of sea creatures including sharks, rays, and giant groupers swimming above and around you.

Animal Interaction Packages
The aquarium also features a stunning underwater zoo, where visitors can watch penguins, otters, and other aquatic animals in their natural habitats.

For the more adventurous, The Dubai Mall Aquarium offers a range of exciting experiences such as cage snorkeling, shark dives, and glass-bottom boat rides that will take you on a thrilling journey through the depths of the ocean.

With its world-class facilities and unparalleled experiences, The Dubai Mall Aquarium is a must-visit attraction for marine life enthusiasts and families alike.

Experience Summary

Get ready to be enchanted by the stunning floral wonderland that is the Dubai Miracle Garden, a one-of-a-kind attraction that boasts over 45 million blooming flowers in a spectacular display of color and creativity.

Located in the heart of Dubai, the Miracle Garden is the world's largest flower garden and features a variety of unique designs and structures, including an impressive flower clock, a heart-shaped pathway, and a magnificent floral castle. You'll also get to see the Guinness World Record for the largest flower arrangement in the shape of an Airbus A380.

With over 60 different species of flowers on display, including rare and exotic varieties, the Dubai Miracle Garden is a must-visit attraction for nature lovers and photography enthusiasts. From vibrant petunias and marigolds to delicate roses and orchids, the garden offers a stunning display of color and fragrance that is sure to leave you in awe.

In addition to the breathtaking displays, the Dubai Miracle Garden also features a range of attractions, such as a butterfly garden, a trampoline park, and a miniature train ride, making it the perfect destination for families and groups.

So why wait? Book your tickets now and get ready to immerse yourself in a world of color and beauty at the Dubai Miracle Garden, a true wonderland of floral creativity and imagination.

Dinner in the Sky in Dubai is a unique gastronomic experience, characterized not only by exquisite dishes but also by its exceptional setting. It takes place on a specially suspended platform, located 50 meters above the ground, equipped with everything necessary for an enjoyable and safe experience.

Dinner in the Sky - is the most panoramic restaurant in the city, where there are no barriers between you and the breathtaking views of the sparkling azure waters of the bay and the metropolis, with its towering facades of modern architectural giants.

The restaurant "Dinner in the Sky" has rightfully earned its reputation as one of the most unique establishments. It has been listed in the top 10 of Forbes magazine as a recommended destination for those who love new experiences.

Experience Summary

LEGOLAND Dubai is a unique LEGO theme park suitable for families with children. LEGOLAND Dubai has more than 40 attractions, 15,000 different figures assembled from 60 million LEGO cubes. The park offers six themed areas with entertainment and educational games: 

LEGO CITY - here children can fly in a LEGO City airport plane, drive a boat on their own and get their first driver's license. 
KINGDOMS - young guests can step into the role of princes and princesses, have a breathtaking adventure through the castle of a king, full of unique items of medieval life, created from LEGO bricks. 
IMAGINATION - LEGO lovers can spend an unforgettable time creating their figures from LEGO cubes, racing LEGO cars or attending classes at the LEGO Academy, Master Builder Academy. 
ADVENTURE - here young adventurers can take a ride on a submarine, take part in water races, as well as search for stolen treasure of Pharaoh. 
MINILAND - in the heart of LEGOLAND Dubai, LEGO cities of the world were created out of 20 million LEGO cubes. 
FACTORY - you can learn how LEGO cubes are created and get a LEGO cube right from the conveyor belt. There is also the BIG Shop - the largest LEGO store in the Middle East.

Experience Summary

La Perle - an exciting blend of artistic performance, visual fantasies, and cutting-edge technology. The director and creator of this 90-minute show is one of the world's most famous directors, Franco Dragone.

You will discover the story of a girl searching for a lost pearl. The show features 65 artists from 23 countries showcasing an incredible range of talents and skills, from dance and acrobatics to water and aerial tricks. 

Acrobats, bikers, and motorcycles defy gravity on stage. Professionals dive from a height of 25 meters into a pool and perform other incredible stunts. Don't miss your chance to experience the thrilling La Perle show.

Experience Summary

IMG Worlds of Adventure is a unique funland spread over a huge area where your favorite characters - from Avengers and Super Babies to life-sized dinosaurs - come to life.

Explore the "Amazing World of Gumball" and the world of Marvel heroes, where you can participate in an interactive air race, ride the "dark" roller coaster, and see the Hulk battle with his nemesis.

Afterwards, head to the lost Jurassic Valley with moving dinosaurs of real size.

Don't miss The Haunted Hotel (15+) and Thor Thunder Spin, a swing that spins around its axis.

You can also stroll along the main boulevard surrounded by stores, cafes and find all kinds of souvenirs with your favorite characters.

This indoor theme park is a perfect solution for days when its either hot or rainy outside.

Experience Summary

Experience the art and culture of the world at the Louvre Abu Dhabi, an architectural masterpiece and world-class museum located on Saadiyat Island.

Designed by French architect Jean Nouvel, the Louvre Abu Dhabi features a stunning dome-like structure that creates a unique play of light and shade, while also evoking the traditional Arabic mashrabiya.

Inside, the museum houses an impressive collection of artwork and artifacts from all over the world, including ancient sculptures, paintings, and manuscripts, as well as contemporary art and installations.

With a focus on promoting cross-cultural dialogue and understanding, the Louvre Abu Dhabi offers a range of educational programs, workshops, and events that allow visitors to learn about art and culture in a fun and interactive way.

In addition to the exhibits, the museum also features a range of amenities, including restaurants, cafes, and shops, making it the perfect destination for a full-day cultural excursion.

With its focus on art, culture, and education, the Louvre Abu Dhabi is a must-visit attraction that offers a unique and unforgettable experience for visitors of all ages and backgrounds.

So why wait? Book your tickets now and get ready to immerse yourself in the world of art and culture at the Louvre Abu Dhabi.

Experience Summary

Step into the world of royalty and history at Qasr Al Watan, an iconic palace and cultural landmark located in Abu Dhabi.

Built to showcase the rich heritage and culture of the United Arab Emirates, Qasr Al Watan is a grand and majestic palace that boasts stunning architecture, intricate design, and luxurious interiors.

Inside, visitors can explore the various rooms and halls of the palace, each of which is adorned with beautiful art, calligraphy, and traditional crafts. The palace also houses an extensive collection of historical artifacts, manuscripts, and documents, providing a unique insight into the history and culture of the UAE.

In addition to the exhibits, Qasr Al Watan also offers a range of interactive experiences, including cultural workshops, traditional performances, and guided tours, allowing visitors to learn about the customs, traditions, and values of the Emirati people.

With its focus on culture, heritage, and education, Qasr Al Watan is a must-visit attraction for anyone looking to experience the beauty and grandeur of the UAE's rich history and culture.

So why wait? Book your tickets now and get ready to step into the world of royalty and history at Qasr Al Watan.

Experience Summary

You can see the famous palm island at a glance from the height of the 52nd floor of The Palm Tower.

From a height of 240 m, a breathtaking view of the Persian Gulf, the man-made island and the skyscrapers of Dubai opens up.

A three-minute elevator ride is accompanied by a virtual show: at first, its walls seem to become transparent, and then there is an illusion of diving into the depths of the sea.

The 'View Exhibition', is an installation dedicated showing the construction of The Palm Jumeirah.

You can visit the observation deck The View at The Palm separately or as part of a Night Dubai Tour of Dubai.

Experience Summary

The Palm Jumeirah Monorail is a monorail line on the Palm Jumeirah island in Dubai, United Arab Emirates. The monorail connects the Palm Jumeirah to the mainland, with a planned further extension to the Red Line of the Dubai Metro. The line opened on April 30, 2009. It is the first monorail in the Middle East Destination First Train Last Train Gateway 9:00 AM 9:45 PM Atlantis 9:15 AM 10:00 PM

Experience Summary

The observatory located on the 52nd and 53rd floors of Address Sky View hotel offers unforgettable experiences. Take an exhilarating ride on a panoramic glass elevator to a height of over 219.5 meters above the ground. Walk on a 25-meter glass floor and enjoy breathtaking views of the city's majestic skyline and shimmering coastline. Sky Views Edge Walk is the most thrilling attraction in Dubai and the first of its kind in the region. It is the highest outdoor walkway on a skyscraper, at a height of over 219.5 meters above the ground. This walk takes visitors on the exterior side of the building, without windows or other protective barriers

Experience Summary

Experience the thrill of skiing in the heart of the desert with our incredible Ski Dubai tour. Located in the Mall of the Emirates, Ski Dubai is the first indoor ski resort in the Middle East and offers a one-of-a-kind experience for winter sports enthusiasts. Step into a winter wonderland as you enter Ski Dubai's massive snow park, which spans over 22,500 square meters. Feel the chill in the air as you explore the various attractions and activities available. Strap on your skis or snowboard and hit the slopes, where you can carve your way down the snowy hills and experience the thrill of winter sports in a unique setting. For those who prefer a more relaxed experience, take a ride on the chairlift and enjoy the breathtaking views of the snow-covered landscape. Marvel at the intricately designed snow sculptures and igloos, and even try your hand at building your own snowman. If you're looking for some family fun, head over to the snow park's tubing hill, where you can slide down the slopes on an inflatable tube. Or, grab a sled and race down the snow-covered hills with your loved ones. After all the excitement, take a break and warm up with a hot chocolate or indulge in some delicious snacks at one of the cozy cafes in the snow park. Don't forget to capture the memories with stunning photos against the backdrop of the snowy landscape. Whether you're a seasoned skier or a beginner looking to try something new, Ski Dubai offers an unforgettable experience for all ages and skill levels. Escape the desert heat and immerse yourself in a winter wonderland like no other.
